# The F.M. Zavala Law Firm — Santa Clarita Divorce Attorney Website

A modern, elegant, and fully SEO-optimized website for The F.M. Zavala Law Firm, a family law practice serving Santa Clarita Valley, California.

**Live pages:** Home, About, Practice Areas, Why Choose Us, Contact (with working consultation request form).

## Tech Stack

- Next.js 16 (App Router, Server Components, static prerendering)
- Tailwind CSS v4 + custom elegant design system
- shadcn/ui (Base UI primitives) + Framer Motion (tasteful, restrained animations)
- Zod + React Server Actions for the contact/consultation form
- Full SEO: Metadata API, sitemap, robots, JSON-LD structured data, Open Graph image generation

## Getting Started

```bash
npm install
npm run dev
```

Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000).

## Key Features

- Calm, trustworthy, professional aesthetic using the specified brand palette (Dusty Blue, Deep Navy, Warm Cream)
- Fully responsive with elegant mobile navigation (Sheet)
- Working free consultation form with server-side validation, honeypot, and success states
- Subtle Framer Motion scroll reveals and testimonial carousel
- Production-ready SEO foundations (sitemap, OG images, Attorney + LegalService schema)

## Form (Production Email)

The consultation form currently logs submissions to the server console. To send real emails in production:

1. Install Resend (recommended): `npm install resend`
2. Add `RESEND_API_KEY` to your environment
3. Replace the placeholder in `app/(marketing)/contact/actions.ts` with an actual `resend.emails.send()` call

See the commented example already present in the action file.

## Customization Notes

- Replace placeholder portrait areas (in About and Home) with professional photography of Frank M. Zavala.
- Update real phone, email, and office address in `components/footer.tsx`, `app/(marketing)/contact/page.tsx`, and schema in `app/layout.tsx`.
- Testimonials are fictional for demonstration — replace with real (permissioned) client stories.
- Adjust practice area descriptions as needed.

## Build & Deploy

```bash
npm run build
```

The site is fully static and deploys beautifully to Vercel, Netlify, or any static host.

## License / Legal

This is a professional marketing website. All legal disclaimers are included in the footer. Content language follows conservative, compliant attorney advertising standards for California.

---

Built following Next.js 16 App Router best practices (see `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` for the authoritative guides used during development).
